      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Allow configuring gateway Permissions-Policy",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add `gateway.http.securityHeaders.permissionsPolicy` as a supported runtime config\n- change the default gateway `Permissions-Policy` to block camera and geolocation without blocking microphone\n- thread the new header through runtime config, schema metadata, and gateway HTTP handling\n- add focused tests for default, override, and explicit disable behavior\n\n## Why\nTalk mode in Control UI needs microphone access, but the current default gateway header hard-blocks it for every response:\n\n```http\nPermissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()\n```\n\nThat makes microphone-based UX regress after updates unless the installed bundle is patched locally. This change moves the fix into source and makes the behavior configurable in the same place as other gateway security headers.\n\n## Validation\n- `corepack pnpm config:schema:gen`\n- `corepack pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway.config.ts src/gateway/http-common.test.ts src/gateway/server-runtime-config.test.ts`\n\n## Notes\nA full repo-wide pre-commit run hit an unrelated existing failure under `extensions/feishu`, so I validated the affected gateway path directly.\n",
